# Filament 4.1 Development Rules

## Filament Version
- Project uses Filament 4.1.10
- Always verify Filament version compatibility before implementing features

## Key Differences in Filament 4

### Forms
- Use `Filament\Schemas\Schema` for form definitions
- Form method signature: `public static function form(Schema $schema): Schema`
- Use `Forms\Components\*` components for form fields (TextInput, Select, DatePicker, etc.)
- **CRITICAL**: Sections come from `Filament\Schemas\Components\Section`, NOT `Filament\Forms\Components\Section`
- Example:
```php
use Filament\Forms\Components\TextInput;
use Filament\Schemas\Components\Section;
use Filament\Schemas\Schema;

public static function form(Schema $schema): Schema
{
    return $schema->schema([
        Section::make('Details')  // From Schemas\Components, NOT Forms\Components
            ->schema([
                TextInput::make('name'),  // From Forms\Components
            ]),
    ]);
}
```

### ViewRecord Pages
- ViewRecord uses `Schema` not `Infolist` for the infolist method
- Method signature: `public function infolist(Schema $schema): Schema`
- **CRITICAL**: Sections come from `Filament\Schemas\Components\Section`, NOT `Filament\Infolists\Components\Section`
- Infolist entries (TextEntry, IconEntry, ImageEntry) come from `Filament\Infolists\Components\*`
- **CRITICAL**: TextSize enum is `Filament\Support\Enums\TextSize`, NOT `Filament\Infolists\Components\TextEntry\TextEntrySize`
- TextSize values: `TextSize::ExtraSmall`, `TextSize::Small`, `TextSize::Medium`, `TextSize::Large`
- Example:
```php
use Filament\Infolists\Components\TextEntry;
use Filament\Schemas\Components\Section;
use Filament\Schemas\Schema;
use Filament\Support\Enums\TextSize;

public function infolist(Schema $schema): Schema
{
    return $schema->schema([
        Section::make('Title')  // From Schemas\Components, NOT Infolists\Components
            ->schema([
                TextEntry::make('field')
                    ->size(TextSize::Large),  // Use Filament\Support\Enums\TextSize
            ]),
    ]);
}
```

### Tables
- Use `Filament\Tables\Table` for table definitions
- Table method signature: `public static function table(Table $table): Table`
- Actions use `Actions\*` namespace, not `Tables\Actions\*`
- Filters use `Tables\Filters\*`

### Navigation Icons
- Use `Filament\Support\Icons\Heroicon`
- Property type: `protected static string|BackedEnum|null $navigationIcon`
- Example: `protected static string|BackedEnum|null $navigationIcon = Heroicon::OutlinedCalendarDays;`

### Resource Pages
- ManageRecords: `Filament\Resources\Pages\ManageRecords`
- CreateRecord: `Filament\Resources\Pages\CreateRecord`
- EditRecord: `Filament\Resources\Pages\EditRecord`
- ViewRecord: `Filament\Resources\Pages\ViewRecord`
- All pages must have `protected static string $resource = ResourceClass::class;`

### Actions
- Table row actions: Use `->actions([Actions\EditAction::make()])`
- Header actions: Use `protected function getHeaderActions(): array`
- Bulk actions: Use `->bulkActions([Actions\BulkActionGroup::make([...])])`

### Filters
- Use `Tables\Filters\Filter::make()` for custom filters
- Toggle filters: `->toggle()`
- No `FiltersLayout::Tabs` enum exists - use toggle filters instead
- Filter queries should use database queries, not collection filtering

### Table Tabs
- Table tabs are implemented using `getTabs()` method in ManageRecords pages
- **CRITICAL**: Tab class is `Filament\Schemas\Components\Tabs\Tab`, NOT `Filament\Tables\Tabs\Tab`
- Method signature: `public function getTabs(): array`
- Use `modifyQueryUsing()` to filter queries for each tab
- Example:
```php
use Filament\Schemas\Components\Tabs\Tab;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Builder;

public function getTabs(): array
{
    return [
        'all' => Tab::make('All')
            ->icon('heroicon-o-microphone')
            ->badge(Model::count()),
        'filtered' => Tab::make('Filtered')
            ->modifyQueryUsing(fn(Builder $query) => $query->where('field', 'value')),
    ];
}
```

### Widgets
- Stats widgets: `Filament\Widgets\StatsOverviewWidget`
- Use `Stat::make()` for individual stats
- Widgets go in `app/Filament/Widgets/`

## Common Mistakes to Avoid
1. âťŚ Don't use `Tables\Actions\*` - use `Actions\*` instead
2. âťŚ Don't use `FiltersLayout::Tabs` - it doesn't exist
3. âťŚ Don't use `Filament\Infolists\Infolist` in ViewRecord - use `Schema`
4. âťŚ **CRITICAL**: Don't use `Filament\Forms\Components\Section` - Sections in forms come from `Filament\Schemas\Components\Section`
5. âťŚ **CRITICAL**: Don't use `Filament\Infolists\Components\Section` - Sections in ViewRecord come from `Filament\Schemas\Components\Section`
6. âťŚ **CRITICAL**: Don't use `Filament\Infolists\Components\TextEntry\TextEntrySize` - Use `Filament\Support\Enums\TextSize` instead
7. âťŚ **CRITICAL**: Don't use `Filament\Tables\Tabs\Tab` - Table tabs use `Filament\Schemas\Components\Tabs\Tab`
8. âťŚ Don't use `Filament\Resources\Pages\Page` for resource pages - use specific page types
9. âťŚ Don't filter collections in table filters - use database queries
10. âťŚ Don't forget to check if record is null before accessing properties

## Best Practices
- Always check existing resource implementations before creating new ones
- Use sections to organize forms logically
- Use collapsible sections for optional/advanced settings
- Add helper text to form fields for better UX
- Use proper column spans (`columnSpanFull()`, `columns(2)`)
- Always add null checks when accessing record properties in closures
- Use proper date/time formatting in infolists
- Add icons to entries for better visual hierarchy

